{"schema_version": 2, "ts": "2026-05-11T12:34:33Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "artifact-template-cleanups-architectural-pattern-optional-indexmd-body-trim-frontmatter-preserved-d4-open-decisions-optional", "parent_epic_loaded": true, "findings": [{"text": "The Intent clarity HIGH rating treats the title/body drift as a resolved disambiguation rule (body authoritative), but the title still advertises 'Architectural Pattern critical-only + Scope Boundaries deletion + index.md frontmatter-only' — three claims the body negates — and the body never states 'the body is authoritative'.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Sub-item #1 contains an internal contradiction: the §3 Touch points bullet says 'remove field from default rendering' while the prose two paragraphs above says 'Standard §3 template includes the field in the canonical format with a note optional...'. These cannot both be executed literally.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Sub-item #3 leaves the H1 title disposition open: Risks says 'Consider whether to keep the H1 title only,' while Verification says '~3 lines body (frontmatter unchanged; H1/intro/wikilinks removed)' — the body's H1 line is undecided in the source.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The Scope boundedness HIGH rating cites concrete touch points but the per-section touch points and the bottom-of-ticket Touch points list disagree: bottom list pairs plan.md with 'Architectural Pattern + Scope Boundaries' (Scope Boundaries is deferred to #182) and entirely omits specify.md (the file sub-item #4 actually touches).", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The Scope boundedness HIGH rating accepts explicit deferral of Scope Boundaries deletion, but the title still advertises it and the bottom Touch points still includes it as an in-scope touch point.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The Scope boundedness HIGH rating ignores sub-item #4's implicit cross-ticket ordering dependency on #183 (Gate 2 removal); blocked-by is empty in the frontmatter, but the body asserts D4 was previously BLOCKED on Gate 2.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The Requirements alignment HIGH rating cites 'audit-driven trimming policy' but two of three sub-items required pressure-test corrections; the audit's track record on these specific items is mixed.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The Requirements alignment HIGH rating cites audit consumer counts (1.4%, 53%) but the audit method demonstrably missed implicit consumers in 4 reference files, undermining those counts as a quality signal.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The parent epic body lists Architectural Pattern in its per-feature artifact bloat findings (1.4% populated), framing it for cuts; the child's resolution is 'keep optional in default template' — a critical-review correction the parent epic body has not been updated to reflect.", "origin": "alignment"}, {"text": "The parent epic flags refine/SKILL.md as carrying a 21-line copy-paste bug and ~700 lines of cross-skill duplication; the child edits refine/SKILL.md at lines 187-193 (index.md update step) without acknowledging whether that region intersects the flagged duplication or copy-paste-bug area.", "origin": "alignment"}, {"text": "The Complexity 'complex' tier reasoning cites '6+ files modified' but the count includes a file that overlaps with the deferred #182 Scope Boundaries work.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The Criticality 'high' rating does not weigh that sub-item #4 changes spec.md authoring conventions while Gate 2's enforcement consumer may still be live in the transient window before #183 lands.", "origin": "primary"}], "dispositions": {"apply": 2, "dismiss": 6, "ask": 4}, "applied_fixes": ["Alignment finding 9 (Architectural Pattern keep-optional vs parent's bloat framing) propagated to research-considerations: validate that prior research's evaluated-not-decorative evidence is still current.", "Alignment finding 10 (refine/SKILL.md edit site near flagged duplication) propagated to research-considerations: verify whether lines 187-193 intersect the parent epic's flagged duplication or copy-paste-bug region."], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 0, "rationale": "The body explicitly self-identifies as the corrected framing ('Post-decomposition critical-review (C3) corrected this'). The implementer reading the body — which is what /cortex-core:refine does — has no ambiguity. Title drift is a documentation hygiene concern, not an intent ambiguity."}, {"finding_index": 3, "rationale": "Per-section Touch points are authoritative; specify.md is explicitly named in sub-item #4 even though absent from the bottom list. Research will operate from the per-section content."}, {"finding_index": 4, "rationale": "The body explicitly states 'This step in #180: NO-OP after refactor; #182 owns the Scope Boundaries removal' — boundary is resolved in the body even if not in the title or bottom list."}, {"finding_index": 6, "rationale": "Meta-philosophical objection. The current ticket IS the corrected version; alignment is evaluated against the corrected scope, not the audit's prior track record."}, {"finding_index": 7, "rationale": "The corrected sub-items specifically addressed the missed-consumer concern (sub-item #3 keeps frontmatter; sub-item #1 keeps the field). The concern was already factored in by the critical review."}, {"finding_index": 10, "rationale": "File count holds without Scope Boundaries: plan.md, orchestrator-review.md, lifecycle/SKILL.md, review.md, refine/SKILL.md, specify.md = 6 files. Complex tier holds on the in-scope count alone."}], "status": "ok"}
